title: To the Memory of a Lady Lately Deceased: A Monody
creator: Lord George Lyttleton
citedtext: Preface: "A prudence undeceiving, undeceived, / That nor too little, nor too much believed; / That scorned unjust Suspicion's coward fear, / and without weakness knew to be sincere
findingaid: This excerpt can be found on page nine, part XII.
